print()
## UNIVARIATE ANALYSIS LOOP
for i in df.columns:
    print('Attribute:\n\n\t', i, ':\t', descriptions[i], '\n')
    print('Univariate Analysis:\n\n\t', analysis[i], '\n')
## PLOTS    
    plt.figure(figsize=(18,3))
    plt.subplot(131)
    plt.hist(df[i], bins = 31)
    plt.title('Counts')
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.subplot(132)
    df[i].plot(kind = 'kde')
    plt.ylabel('')
    plt.title('Kernel Density Estimate')
    plt.subplot(133)
    red_square = dict(markerfacecolor='r', marker='s')
    plt.boxplot(df[i], vert = False, notch = True, flierprops = red_square)
    plt.title('Outliers')
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.show()
### VALUES
    print('\nValue Ranges:\n\t', df[i].min(), '-', df[i].max(), '\n')
    print('Median Value:\n\t', df[i].median(), '\n')
    print(f'Mean Value:\n\t {df[i].mean():.2f}\n')
    print('Quantile Values:','\n\t Q1:', df[i].quantile(.25),'\n\t Q2/Median:', df[i].quantile(.5), '\n\t Q3:', df[i].quantile(.75),
      f'\n\t IQR: {df[i].quantile(.75)-df[i].quantile(.25):.2f}\n')
    print(f'Standard Deviation:\n\t {df[i].std():.2f}')
    print()
    print('*************************************')
    print()

Identifying the outliers showed me that many instances shared identical admixtures, the only difference was their age and strength. df_sims is a dataframe of these instances.¶

In [16]:
df_copy['sims'] = df_copy.duplicated(keep = False, subset = ['cement', 'slag', 'ash', 'water', 'superplastic', 'coarseagg', 'fineagg']).values
df_sims = df_copy.loc[df_copy.sims == True]
# c/w is concrete to water ratio, something that seems to be of some importance
df_sims['c/w'] = df_sims.loc[:, 'cement'] / df_sims.loc[:, 'water']

In [50]:
yes = []
for i in df_copy.superplastic:
    if i > 0:
        yes.append(1)
    else:
        yes.append(0)
df_copy['yes_superplastic'] = yes
In [51]:
yes = []
for i in df_copy.ash:
    if i > 0:
        yes.append(1)
    else:
        yes.append(0)
df_copy['yes_ash'] = yes
In [52]:
yes = []
for i in df_copy.slag:
    if i > 0:
        yes.append(1)
    else:
        yes.append(0)
df_copy['yes_slag'] = yes

Specific Densities of the Individual Components. Units are g/cm^3¶

In [53]:
dcement = 1.442
dslag = 1.052
dash = 1.395
dwater = .997
dsuperplastic = 1.2
dcoarseagg = 1.602
dfineagg = 0.00171

Changing the units of our date to g/cm^3¶

In [54]:
df_copy.iloc[:, :-6] = df_copy.iloc[:, :-6]/1000
In [55]:
df_copy['weights'] = (df_copy['cement'] * dcement) + (df_copy['slag'] * dslag) + (df_copy['ash'] * dash) + (df_copy['water'] * dwater) + (df_copy['superplastic'] * dsuperplastic) + (df_copy['coarseagg'] * dcoarseagg) + (df_copy['fineagg'] * dfineagg)
In [56]:
df_copy['net'] = df_copy.cement + df_copy.slag + df_copy.ash + df_copy.water + df_copy.superplastic + df_copy.coarseagg + df_copy.fineagg
In [57]:
df_copy['Pcement'] = df_copy.cement / df_copy.net
df_copy['Pslag'] = df_copy.slag / df_copy.net
df_copy['Pash'] = df_copy.ash / df_copy.net
df_copy['Pwater'] = df_copy.water / df_copy.net
df_copy['Psuperplastic'] = df_copy.superplastic / df_copy.net
df_copy['Pcoarseagg'] = df_copy.coarseagg / df_copy.net
df_copy['Pfineagg'] = df_copy.fineagg / df_copy.net
In [58]:
df_copy['Density'] = (df_copy['Pcement'] * dcement) + (df_copy['Pslag'] * dslag) + (df_copy['Pash'] * dash) + (df_copy['Pwater'] * dwater) + (df_copy['Psuperplastic'] * dsuperplastic) + (df_copy['Pcoarseagg'] * dcoarseagg) + (df_copy['Pfineagg'] * dfineagg)
In [59]:
df_copy['cement/water'] = df_copy.cement / df_copy.water
In [60]:
df_copy['h20-binder'] = df_copy.water / (df_copy.cement + df_copy.slag + df_copy.ash)
In [61]:
df_copy['coarse/fine'] = df_copy.coarseagg / df_copy.fineagg

Scaling down the strength values to help with modeling.¶

In [62]:
df_copy['strength'] = df_copy['strength']/100
In [63]:
df_copy.drop(columns = ['sims'], inplace = True)
